President Obama has announced the appointment of Ambassador Donald Booth as the new U.S. Special Envoy for Sudan and South Sudan. Ambassador Booth is an experienced diplomat who has worked extensively in Africa, including serving as the Ambassador to Ethiopia. The President believes that Ambassador Booth's diplomatic skills and knowledge of the continent will help advance U.S. interests in achieving lasting peace between Sudan and South Sudan. Ambassador Booth will be responsible for ensuring the implementation of previous agreements and resolving outstanding issues, such as borders and the final status of Abyei. He will also work towards ending conflicts in Blue Nile, Southern Kordofan, and Darfur, as well as promoting inclusive governance and human rights in both countries. The President believes that peace and progress are possible when the governments of Sudan and South Sudan prioritize the interests of their people.